# STONKZ — project rules

You are building STONKZ (stonkz.meme): a token launchpad on Robinhood Chain
(Arbitrum-based L2, ~100ms blocks, ERC-4337, Uniswap v4 settlement venue).
Solo founder + you. Trust is the product: the competitor (Noxa) took $12M in
fees and went dark; our positioning is "the launchpad that can't run away
with your money."

## Read order (before writing any code)
1. docs/mechanism-spec.md        — THE mechanism. Formulas are final.
2. reference/engine.test.js      — 19 locked behaviors (run: node reference/engine.test.js)
3. docs/launch-plan.md           — business context, decisions log, security ladder

## Hard rules
- STOP forensics must be pushed before any ruling request. Every STOP report
  (`docs/stop-task-*.md` and the commits that produced it) is pushed to the
  working branch before asking the human to rule. Un-pushed forensics do not
  exist — do not present a STOP as complete until `git push` has succeeded.
- NEVER change mechanism math without asking. The spec was designed and
  simulator-validated over many sessions; formulas (κ̂ split, guard headroom,
  weight pacing, gate, size tilt α) are decisions, not suggestions.
- Every Solidity rule must be DIFFERENTIALLY TESTED against reference/engine.js.
  If Solidity and the reference disagree, the reference wins until the human
  rules otherwise.
- The 10 invariants in spec §9 are non-negotiable. New code paths must not
  weaken them; add invariant tests before features.
- All mechanism fractions are of LAUNCH supply; all economics in mcap/$ terms
  (units principle, spec §0). No token-count-dependent logic.
- 100ms blocks: no per-block iteration on-chain. Lazy O(1) accumulator
  accounting only (masterchef-style, exits bucketed at price ticks).
- Never sponsor gas on bids. Min bid + flat fee stay.
- Security posture: guarded launch caps, immutable contracts, admin to hardened
  keys at construction, deployer ends powerless. Do not add upgradeability.
- Regression-lock the failure modes listed in contracts/test/StonkzAuction.t.sol
  section C — each was found the hard way.

## Style
- Solidity 0.8.26, via-ir, NatSpec references spec sections (e.g. "spec §6").
- Frontend voice: memeworld/win95, deliberate misspellings ("likwidity",
  "is not financal advice becuase we cannot spell financal") — see
  reference/memeworld-mockup.html. Never correct the misspellings.
- Ticker: $STONKZ4663. Domain: stonkz.meme (stonkz.green redirects).
